com.revolsys.jts.geom.impl

Class BoundingBoxDoubleGf

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.revolsys.jts.geom.impl.BoundingBoxDoubleGf
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BoundingBox, Serializable

    public class BoundingBoxDoubleGf
extends Object
implements Serializable, BoundingBox
    Defines a rectangular region of the 2D coordinate plane. It is often used to represent the bounding box of a Geometry, e.g. the minimum and maximum x and y values of the Coordinatess.

    Note that Envelopes support infinite or half-infinite regions, by using the values of Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY and Double.NEGATIVE_INFINITY.

    When BoundingBoxDoubleGf objects are created or initialized, the supplies extent values are automatically sorted into the correct order.

    Version:
    1.7

      • move

        public BoundingBox move(double xDisplacement,
               double yDisplacement)

        Create a new BoundingBox by moving the min/max x coordinates by xDisplacement and the min/max y coordinates by yDisplacement. If the bounding box is null or the xDisplacement and yDisplacement are 0 then this bounding box will be returned.

        Specified by:
        move in interface BoundingBox
        Parameters:
        xDisplacement - The distance to move the min/max x coordinates.
        yDisplacement - The distance to move the min/max y coordinates.
        Returns:
        The moved bounding box.

      • toGeometry

        public Geometry toGeometry()
        Description copied from interface: BoundingBox
        Creates a Geometry with the same extent as the given envelope. The Geometry returned is guaranteed to be valid. To provide this behaviour, the following cases occur:

        If the BoundingBoxDoubleGf is:

        • null : returns an empty Point
        • a point : returns a non-empty Point
        • a line : returns a two-point LineString
        • a rectangle : returns a Polygon> whose points are (minx, miny), (minx, maxy), (maxx, maxy), (maxx, miny), (minx, miny).
        Specified by:
        toGeometry in interface BoundingBox
        Returns:
        an empty Point (for null BoundingBoxDoubleGfs), a Point (when min x = max x and min y = max y) or a Polygon (in all other cases)
